Do you know yuru yuru Haizai ecovillage ? This space has been created by the artist Hiryu. He bought an old factory and built a wonderful and inspiring open space for everyone with recycling materials. He created compost toilets, kitchen/cafe, rooms, library, music and theater space, bath, garden.... In this space, several times per months, there are different workshops. Last week, people learnt how to make natto. Another time, people learnt how to make basket bamboo. At one kilometer, there are several mobile houses surrounded by forest, river, garden, sauna, compost toilet. There, the Bochi Bochi community was born with Naru, for people who want to create their own mobile house and share this lifestyle. In Yuru Yuru Haizai ecovillage, you feel in another world : a world where you can live relaxly, where you can live slowly, where people smiling, where people singing, where you are connected to nature, where the small troubles and the unnecessary things  disappear, where you can breathe fresh air, where you can hear birds singing, where you want to take action, where you want to be creative, where life becomes so simple and easy, where you want to share positive vibes. 
Thanks to Hiryu, Naru and all the beautiful souls passing there ! 

